Both required outputs are in place.

- `transcript.json` (141 KB, valid against `transcript_schema.json`): 25 iterations, 209 named hypotheses + 209 matching analyses with signed effect estimates, p-values, and significance flags.
- `analysis_summary.txt`: a narrative walkthrough of the iterations, themed by treatment main effects, biomarker-targeted subgroups, prognostic main effects, formal interactions, multivariable models, modifiers/PGx, and sociodemographics — calling out which hypotheses were supported (palbociclib in ER+/HER2-, palbociclib × PIK3CA negative interaction, standard clinical prognosticators, TNBC/luminal-A) and which were refuted in this cohort (tamoxifen × ER+, trastuzumab × HER2+, sacituzumab govitecan × TNBC/HER2-low, pembrolizumab × MSI-high, demographic/SNP/comorbidity effects).
